SIMPLE: malleus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malleus
<hw>Mal"le*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Mallei</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., hammer. See
<er>Mall</er> a beetle.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The
outermost of the three small auditory bones, ossicles; the hammer. It is
attached to the tympanic membrane by a long process, the handle or
manubrium. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Far</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the hard lateral pieces of
the mastax of Rotifera. See <er>Mastax</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of bivalve shells; the
hammer shell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mallophaga</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
